         <critic>Jorge Morales</critic>
      </review>
      <review>
         <snippet>With a little more subtlety - and a lot less predictability - the movie might have played more like a thoughtful drama and less like an outrageous exercise in wish fulfillment.</snippet>
         <url>http://www.nytimes.com/2006/03/16/movies/16hate.html</url>
         <critic>Jeannette Catsoulis</critic>
      </review>
      <review>
         <snippet>This melodrama by writer-director Tommy Stovall has a good premise, but he undercuts it with contrived plot twists, pedestrian pacing, and mostly two-dimensional characters.</snippet>
